				</common:classification>
			</classificationInformation>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">In emissions, &quot;petroleum-related&quot; refers to pollutants from petroleum products, including volatile organic compounds (VOCs) and polycyclic aromatic hydrocarbons (PAHs), which contribute to smog and are harmful to health. Sulfur in petroleum forms sulfides like sulfur dioxide, leading to acid rain, and combustion produces particulate matter and nitrogen oxides (NOx), which can damage human lungs and deplete the ozone layer. Controlling these emissions is crucial for environmental protection and human health.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">在排放中，&quot;与石油有关 &quot;指的是石油产品产生的污染物，包括挥发性有机化合物 (VOC) 和多环芳烃 (PAH)，这些物质会导致烟雾并危害健康。石油中的硫会形成二氧化硫等硫化物，导致酸雨，燃烧会产生颗粒物质和氮氧化物（NOx），它们会损害人的肺部并破坏臭氧层。控制这些排放对环境保护和人类健康至关重要。</common:generalComment>
